  "description": "Fix Image Error Styling in Program Card Header\n\nUpdate the CSS for image error states within the program card header component to use position:relative and min-height:100% instead of the current positioning value.\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate the .image-error class or equivalent styling within the program-card-header component\n- Change the position property from its current value (likely absolute, relative, or fixed) to initial\n- Verify the change doesn't break the layout in normal display state\n- Test how the error state image displays across different card sizes and viewport widths\n- Ensure the image error placeholder or icon remains properly visible and aligned after the change\n- Check for any related styles that may need adjustment due to position change (z-index, top, left, right, bottom properties)",
